claim.claim-text:
1. A process for optimizing a therapeutic drug to reduce or prevent export of the therapeutic drug from a cell by an exporter protein, the method comprising the steps of:
a) measuring hydrophobicity of the therapeutic drug by measuring ΔGHA(drug);
b) generating a modified therapeutic drug by modifying the therapeutic drug to increase the hydrophobicity of the therapeutic drug;
c) measuring hydrophobicity of the modified therapeutic drug by measuring ΔGHA(modified drug), and determining a change in hydrophobicity δΔGHA calculated as ΔGHA(modified drug)−ΔGHA(drug); and
d) determining a change in rate of export from the cell of the modified therapeutic drug compared to the therapeutic drug;

10. A process for optimizing a therapeutic drug to reduce or prevent export of the therapeutic drug from a cell by an exporter protein, the method comprising the steps of:
a) measuring hydrophobicity of the therapeutic drug by measuring a ΔHA(drug); and
b) modifying the therapeutic drug to generate a modified therapeutic drug with a hydrophobicity measured as ΔGHA(modified drug) such that a change in hydrophobicity of δΔGHA calculated as ΔGHA(modified drug)−ΔGHA(drug) falls between the range of about −2 kcal/mol to about −20 kcal/mol;
